$ v$sesstat

`v$sesstat` is similar to → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/mystat except except that it shows cumulated statistics for all sessions.

`v$sessions` is also similar to → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/sysstat except that v$sysstat accumulates the statistics as soon as a session terminates. 


gh|oracle-patterns|/Installed/dynamic-performance-views/sesstat/show-statistics.sql||

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/mystat,
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/statname

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/[Oracle Dynamic Performance Views]
